Put the bottarga, garlic, three-quarters of the lemon juice, 2 tablespoons of the olive oil, half the tomatoes and the torn basil in a pestle and mortar and pound to a loose dressing.Toss the artichokes with the remaining lemon juice and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.Blanch the broccoli in boiling water for 2 minutes, then refresh under cold running water.Arrange the broccoli, artichokes, fennel and celery on a serving plate and sprinkle over the remaining tomatoes. Drizzle over the dressing and garnish with the celery leaves and basil leaves. Finely grate over a little bottarga and serve.